<DOC><DOCNO> DOE1-18-0324 </DOCNO><TEXT>A general formula for the magnitude-redshift relation in a linearly perturbedFriedmann universe is derived. The formula does not assume any specificgauge condition, but the gauge-invariance of it is explicitly shown.Then the application of the formula to the spatially flat backgroundmodel is considered and the implications are discussed.</TEXT></DOC>